The Delta State chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) says it is once again ready to produce the next governor of the State. This was disclosed by Honourable Onoriode Agofure, Deputy Leader, Ughelli North Legislative Arm, Ughelli North Local Government Council in an interview with SATURDAY INDEPENDENT at the Mega Rally of the PDP in Asaba, he said that the PDP in Delta state remains strong, formidable, united and rooted in every political unit across the state. The Chieftain of the PDP also expressed confidence that whoever emerges as the PDP governorship candidate at the primary will win the general election, adding that Governor Ifeanyi Okowaâ€™s performance and achievements had already won the 2023 governorship election for PDP. Russia Sees Record Virus Cases Second Day Running NGOs Demand Justice For 5yr-Old Pupil Murdered By Proprietor Hon. Agofure, who is said to be eyeing Delta State House of Assembly to represent Ughelli North Constituency 11come 2023 disclosed that he is willing and determined to offer quality, purposeful, accountable and effective representation to the people of Ughelli North Constituency 2 at the Delta State House Assembly if given the mandate. He, however, urged youths in the state to get involved in politics and vie for elective offices, while also appealing to Governor Ifeanyi Okowa and the leadership of PDP in the state to consider more youths for elective positions in 2023. Hon. Agofure further expressed optimism that the PDP will produce a Governorship candidate at the primary that will be sellable and acceptable to party leaders, faithful and Deltans, noting that it is the wish and desire of Governor Ifeanyi Okowa to handover to a successor that will ensure continuity and consolidate on achievements made.